      "rationale": "Patch tests and single-element benchmark problems (pure bending, axial, torsion) were executed for all three solver configurations. Results match analytical solutions within 0.5%. Code verification documentation archived in the project technical record."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/discretization-gci-less-than-2pct",
      "rationale": "Systematic mesh refinement study conducted across three mesh densities (coarse ~80k elements, medium ~320k, fine ~1.28M) for the non-cannulated construct. Richardson extrapolation and GCI computed for stiffness and yield force QoIs; GCI < 1.8% for all QoIs at the medium mesh, which was adopted for production runs. Discretization error is bounded and documented."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/solver-residual-convergence-1e-6",
      "rationale": "Newton-Raphson residual convergence criterion set to 1e-6 relative norm for all nonlinear quasi-static analyses. Force and displacement residuals monitored at every load increment; no load step required bisection beyond two levels. Solver error contribution estimated < 0.3% of QoI magnitude."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/use-error-independent-review-checklist",
      "rationale": "An independent senior analyst performed a blind re-run of the FEA setup from the documented simulation plan. Boundary conditions, material assignments, contact definitions, and load application were verified against the ASTM F1717 protocol specification. No discrepancies found. Achieved level 3 exceeds the required level 2, providing additional confidence margin."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/model-form-elasto-plastic-contact-justified",
      "rationale": "Continuum elasto-plastic constitutive model (bilinear isotropic hardening) selected for titanium alloy screw and UHMWPE vertebral body surrogates. Geometric nonlinearity enabled for large-displacement regime beyond yield. Frictionless contact between screw and rod justified by lubricated test conditions per ASTM F1717. Model form selection documented with literature support and sensitivity analysis confirming < 4% QoI sensitivity to friction coefficient in range 0–0.15."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/model-inputs-material-certs-dimensional-metrology",
      "rationale": "Material properties (Young's modulus, yield stress, tangent modulus) sourced from coupon tensile tests on the same lot of Ti-6Al-4V used to manufacture the test constructs; n=5 coupons per lot, mean ± SD reported. Construct geometry verified against CMM measurements of three representative screws and rods; dimensional deviations < 0.05 mm incorporated into sensitivity analysis. Input uncertainty propagated via Monte Carlo (1000 samples) to quantify QoI uncertainty bands."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/test-samples-n11-two-labs-traceability",
      "rationale": "N=11 non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs tested across two independent laboratories (FDA CDRH and DePuy Synthes R&D). All specimens from the same production lot with full dimensional and material traceability. Inter-laboratory variability assessed; coefficient of variation < 5% for all three QoIs, confirming sample representativeness."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/test-conditions-astm-f1717-single-load-case",
      "rationale": "Testing conducted under a single ASTM F1717 static compression-bending load case at room temperature in ambient air. While the protocol is standardized and well-controlled, only one test condition was evaluated (no variation in offset distance or loading rate). This limits achieved level to 2, one below the required level of 3. This gap is acknowledged in the decision record and accepted given that the single ASTM F1717 condition directly maps to the regulatory submission requirement and supplementary sensitivity analyses bound the effect of rate variation.",
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/nagaraja-cou1-noncannulated-decision-2024/factor/test-conditions"
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/input-equivalency-cou-vs-validation-mapping",
      "rationale": "Formal mapping table prepared comparing COU input parameters (screw geometry, material, loading, boundary conditions) against validation experiment inputs. All primary QoI-driving parameters are equivalent between COU and validation activity. Minor differences in fixture compliance quantified and shown to contribute < 2% to QoI uncertainty via sensitivity study."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/output-comparison-evalue-less-than-1p96",
      "rationale": "Validation metric E/uval computed for all three QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm displacement) following ASME V&V 40 Section 5.3. E/uval values: stiffness 0.81, yield force 1.12, force-at-40mm 0.94. All three values < 1.96, satisfying the pre-established acceptance criterion. Percentage differences: stiffness 3.2%, yield force 5.8%, force-at-40mm 4.1%, all within the <10% bound. Detailed comparison plots and statistical summaries archived."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/qoi-relevance-regulatory-submission-linkage",
      "rationale": "The three QoIs (construct stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm displacement) are the exact quantities required by FDA guidance for pedicle screw 510(k) submissions and directly specified in ASTM F1717. Their clinical relevance is established: stiffness governs load sharing; yield force indicates onset of permanent deformation; force at 40 mm displacement characterizes post-yield behavior relevant to construct failure scenarios."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/validation-cou-relevance-same-geometry-protocol",
      "rationale": "The validation activity directly tests the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct — the identical device geometry, material, and loading protocol as the COU. There is no interpolation or extrapolation required between the validation domain and the COU domain. The two-laboratory design provides independent confirmation of experimental reproducibility, strengthening the relevance argument."
    }
